<heading bold="true" box="[264,980,563,590]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,980,563,590]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Key to the species of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[572,806,564,590]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Volucella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pellucens">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[572,806,564,590]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Volucella pellucens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1325,639,1425]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
1. Legs with apexes of femora, bases of tibiae, and basotarsomeres yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[321,477,679,705]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="14.[264,368,1756,1780]" captionTargetBox="[303,1296,632,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-177@14.[291,1309,628,1747]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 5. Volucella species (dorsal and lateral view). A–D, V. thompsoni n.sp. (A, B, male, C, D, female); E–H, V.inflata (E, F, male, G, H, female); I–L, V. nigricans (I, J, male, K, L, female); M–P, V. pellucens pellucens (M, N, male, O, P, female); Q–T, V. pellucens tabanoides (Q, R, male, S, T, female)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920442/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs. 5F, H</figureCitation>
); head with upper post­ocular orbit clearly seen in lateral view (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[264,368,1419,1443]" captionTargetBox="[302,1280,499,1378]" captionTargetId="figure-178@8.[286,1301,486,1395]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2. Volucella inflata (Linnaeus). A–C, male head in anterior, dorsal, and lateral view; D–F, female head in anterior, dorsal, and lateral view; G, male genitalia, lateral view; H, surstylus, inner view; I, male genitalia, posterodorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920436" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920436/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs. 2C, F</figureCitation>
)................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fabricius)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[1110,1322,719,745]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Volucella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inflata">
<emphasis box="[1110,1186,719,744]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">inflata</emphasis>
(Fabricius)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1325,639,1425]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
­ Legs almost entirely dark brown to black (e.g. 
<figureCitation box="[859,998,759,785]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="14.[264,368,1756,1780]" captionTargetBox="[303,1296,632,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-177@14.[291,1309,628,1747]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 5. Volucella species (dorsal and lateral view). A–D, V. thompsoni n.sp. (A, B, male, C, D, female); E–H, V.inflata (E, F, male, G, H, female); I–L, V. nigricans (I, J, male, K, L, female); M–P, V. pellucens pellucens (M, N, male, O, P, female); Q–T, V. pellucens tabanoides (Q, R, male, S, T, female)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920442/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs. 5B, D</figureCitation>
); head with upper post­ocular orbit barely seen in lateral view (e.g. 
<figureCitation box="[786,917,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[264,367,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[296,1276,712,1758]" captionTargetId="figure-141@5.[280,1317,689,1785]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Volucella thompsoni n.sp. A–C, male head in anterior, dorsal, and lateral view; D–F, female head in anterior, dorsal, and lateral view; G, male genitalia, lateral view; H, surstylus, inner view; I, male genitalia, posterodorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920434" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920434/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs. 1C, F</figureCitation>
)................................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1325,639,1425]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
2. Abdominal tergite 2 predominantly black with a pair of pale transverse areas, at most 2/3 of tergite length (
<figureCitation box="[559,687,879,905]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="14.[264,368,1756,1780]" captionTargetBox="[303,1296,632,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-177@14.[291,1309,628,1747]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 5. Volucella species (dorsal and lateral view). A–D, V. thompsoni n.sp. (A, B, male, C, D, female); E–H, V.inflata (E, F, male, G, H, female); I–L, V. nigricans (I, J, male, K, L, female); M–P, V. pellucens pellucens (M, N, male, O, P, female); Q–T, V. pellucens tabanoides (Q, R, male, S, T, female)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920442/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs. 5I, K</figureCitation>
) 
<emphasis box="[703,1084,879,904]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">....................................................</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Coquillett" authorityName="Coquillett. A" authorityYear="1898" box="[1087,1322,879,905]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Volucella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricans">
<emphasis box="[1087,1197,879,904]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">nigricans</emphasis>
Coquillett
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1325,639,1425]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
­ Abdominal tergite 2 almost entirely pale except for narrow median longitudinal stripe in yellow brown to dark brown (e.g. 
<figureCitation box="[742,878,959,985]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="14.[264,368,1756,1780]" captionTargetBox="[303,1296,632,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-177@14.[291,1309,628,1747]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 5. Volucella species (dorsal and lateral view). A–D, V. thompsoni n.sp. (A, B, male, C, D, female); E–H, V.inflata (E, F, male, G, H, female); I–L, V. nigricans (I, J, male, K, L, female); M–P, V. pellucens pellucens (M, N, male, O, P, female); Q–T, V. pellucens tabanoides (Q, R, male, S, T, female)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920442/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs. 5A, C</figureCitation>
) ........................................................ 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1325,639,1425]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
3. Abdominal tergite 2 longer than tergite 3 when measured medially; male basoflagellomere in lateral view slightly constricted in middle (
<figureCitation box="[1090,1186,1039,1065]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[264,367,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[296,1276,712,1758]" captionTargetId="figure-141@5.[280,1317,689,1785]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Volucella thompsoni n.sp. A–C, male head in anterior, dorsal, and lateral view; D–F, female head in anterior, dorsal, and lateral view; G, male genitalia, lateral view; H, surstylus, inner view; I, male genitalia, posterodorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920434" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920434/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
); male eye contiguity about half as long as frontal triangle (
<figureCitation box="[889,980,1079,1105]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[264,367,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[296,1276,712,1758]" captionTargetId="figure-141@5.[280,1317,689,1785]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Volucella thompsoni n.sp. A–C, male head in anterior, dorsal, and lateral view; D–F, female head in anterior, dorsal, and lateral view; G, male genitalia, lateral view; H, surstylus, inner view; I, male genitalia, posterodorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920434" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920434/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
); female eyes densely pilose (
<figureCitation box="[321,406,1119,1145]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[264,367,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[296,1276,712,1758]" captionTargetId="figure-141@5.[280,1317,689,1785]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Volucella thompsoni n.sp. A–C, male head in anterior, dorsal, and lateral view; D–F, female head in anterior, dorsal, and lateral view; G, male genitalia, lateral view; H, surstylus, inner view; I, male genitalia, posterodorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920434" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920434/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
) 
<emphasis box="[417,1260,1119,1144]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
.................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Choi &amp; Ôhara &amp; Han, 2006" authorityName="Choi &amp; Ôhara &amp; Han" authorityYear="2006" box="[1138,1260,1119,1144]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Volucella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thompsoni" status="n.sp.">thompsoni</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1267,1322,1119,1145]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1325,639,1425]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
­ Abdominal tergite 2 slightly but clearly shorter than tergite 3 when measured medially; male basoflagellomere in lateral view transversely elliptic (
<figureCitation box="[1092,1190,1199,1225]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="12.[264,367,1406,1430]" captionTargetBox="[294,1301,342,1351]" captionTargetId="figure-159@12.[267,1326,326,1380]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 4. Volucella pellucens (Linnaeus). A, male head, anterior view; B, male head, dorsal view (pellucens pellucens type); C, male head, dorsal view (pellucens tabanoides type); D, male head, lateral view; E–G, female head in anterior, dorsal, and lateral view; H, male genitalia, lateral view; I, surstylus, inner view; J, male genitalia, posterodorsal view. b epand lb = basal epandrial lobe." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920440" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920440/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
); male eye contiguity about as long as frontal triangle (
<figureCitation box="[824,962,1239,1265]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="12.[264,367,1406,1430]" captionTargetBox="[294,1301,342,1351]" captionTargetId="figure-159@12.[267,1326,326,1380]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 4. Volucella pellucens (Linnaeus). A, male head, anterior view; B, male head, dorsal view (pellucens pellucens type); C, male head, dorsal view (pellucens tabanoides type); D, male head, lateral view; E–G, female head in anterior, dorsal, and lateral view; H, male genitalia, lateral view; I, surstylus, inner view; J, male genitalia, posterodorsal view. b epand lb = basal epandrial lobe." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920440" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920440/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs. 4B, C</figureCitation>
); female eyes bare (
<figureCitation box="[1197,1289,1239,1265]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="12.[264,367,1406,1430]" captionTargetBox="[294,1301,342,1351]" captionTargetId="figure-159@12.[267,1326,326,1380]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 4. Volucella pellucens (Linnaeus). A, male head, anterior view; B, male head, dorsal view (pellucens pellucens type); C, male head, dorsal view (pellucens tabanoides type); D, male head, lateral view; E–G, female head in anterior, dorsal, and lateral view; H, male genitalia, lateral view; I, surstylus, inner view; J, male genitalia, posterodorsal view. b epand lb = basal epandrial lobe." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920440" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920440/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
) 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1325,639,1425]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
4. Female scutum posteriorly without distinct brown triangular macula, or occasionally with faint brownish tinge (
<figureCitation box="[624,728,1319,1345]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="14.[264,368,1756,1780]" captionTargetBox="[303,1296,632,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-177@14.[291,1309,628,1747]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 5. Volucella species (dorsal and lateral view). A–D, V. thompsoni n.sp. (A, B, male, C, D, female); E–H, V.inflata (E, F, male, G, H, female); I–L, V. nigricans (I, J, male, K, L, female); M–P, V. pellucens pellucens (M, N, male, O, P, female); Q–T, V. pellucens tabanoides (Q, R, male, S, T, female)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920442/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs. 5O</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[741,812,1319,1345]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="15.[264,368,1188,1212]" captionTargetBox="[280,1299,824,1150]" captionTargetId="figure-225@15.[270,1317,806,1163]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 6. Female thoracic patterns of Volucella pellucens subspecies. A, B, V. pellucens pellucens; C, D, V. pellucens tabanoides." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920444" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920444/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">6A, B</figureCitation>
) 
<emphasis box="[827,1071,1319,1344]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
.................. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[961,1071,1319,1344]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Volucella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pellucens">pellucens</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[1078,1322,1319,1345]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Volucella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pellucens">
<emphasis box="[1078,1188,1319,1344]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">pellucens</emphasis>
(Linnaeus)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1325,639,1425]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
­ Female scutum posteriorly with distinct brown triangular macula (
<figureCitation box="[1088,1187,1359,1385]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="14.[264,368,1756,1780]" captionTargetBox="[303,1296,632,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-177@14.[291,1309,628,1747]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 5. Volucella species (dorsal and lateral view). A–D, V. thompsoni n.sp. (A, B, male, C, D, female); E–H, V.inflata (E, F, male, G, H, female); I–L, V. nigricans (I, J, male, K, L, female); M–P, V. pellucens pellucens (M, N, male, O, P, female); Q–T, V. pellucens tabanoides (Q, R, male, S, T, female)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920442/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs. 5S</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1201,1273,1359,1385]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="15.[264,368,1188,1212]" captionTargetBox="[280,1299,824,1150]" captionTargetId="figure-225@15.[270,1317,806,1163]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 6. Female thoracic patterns of Volucella pellucens subspecies. A, B, V. pellucens pellucens; C, D, V. pellucens tabanoides." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920444" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920444/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">6C, D</figureCitation>
)..... 
<emphasis box="[315,1028,1399,1424]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
.................................................................................. 
